34:
Did you really think this was enough
to deny the Oxtans and deal them a
fatal blow?
38:
All you achieved was inflicting pain
on yourself!
41:
I beg you. Stop hurting yourself like
this.
48:
You keep believing in the light no
matter what... like an idiot... But look
at me...
52: You too believe in the light. Don't you?
55:
That is why you were saddened and
angered at seeing it tainted. At
seeing the light within each of us left
to rot.
58: Isn't that the reason you cry?
67:
There are still so many things I do
not understand! Things I do not
know and things I know wrong! Too
many to even count...
70:
That's why I want you to tell me. Tell
me about your anger and your
sadness. Tell me your everything!
82:
I can't think straight anymore... not
today...
90:
O-of course! We can chat later! It's a
promise!
94:
Sheesh... The Nialases sure are
something else.
101:
Whew. Being a noble can be hard,
huh.
103:
That's all you have to say after
hearing about everything?
106:
You people live in a different world
from mine. I'm just a simple shop
owner, you know?
108:
Hmm, yes. One that still made sure
to help us with provisions, despite
feigning indifference.
111:
Hey, you expect a guy to stand
around doing nothing while his
captain's out there doing his best?
113:
Still, the fact that you're back means
that things have calmed down...
Right?
115:
Yes. Of course, House Oxtan and
House Kwetur still need to be dealt
with...
117:
But His Highness and House Swes
will take care of that. Things will turn
out all right.
120:
Prince Varen, huh? He's a good
person, but he's got his dense
moments...
122:
Are you sure you should be back
here and not there?
125:
Of course. There still are many
people here whom I am indebted to.
128:
But once it's all over... I figure helping
out His Highness won't be a bad
idea...
138:
Y-Your Highness?! Why are you
here?! Are you alone?!
142: Not to worry! I have the old man
145: Oh no. I think I've lost him.
149: Your Highness... Why have you come?
153:
Oh, taking care of the aftermath is
out of my hands, so I thought I
would take my journey to Palpebra
earlier than originally planned.
156:
I still know little, and my views are
very limited. I lack perspective.
158:
I need to know more about the
world before I meet him again.
162:
And I would like your help with that,
Yuwel!
166:
My apologies, Your Highness, but
unfortunately, I am already needed
elsewhere.
171:
S-seriously?! So you won't come
with me?!
175:
I will show you that "elsewhere." If
you want to know more about the
world, you could ask for no better
opportunity.
180:
Oh! That's perfect! Exactly what I
needed!
183:
Onward, Yuwel! Whatever the future
holds, we shall meet it with light in
our hearts!
187:
Of course, Your Highness. It would be
my honor.
